On Escalation Ticket # 00427371 the new comment has been added: Marius Ghiurcau:

@WaitingOnEngineer

I don't think there is anything that we can do here. They need to check their network. In one of the screenshots provided it seems that they are not even able to access the server GUI from the browser. They have to figure our why.
I remember that for other cases, similar to this one, sometimes the issues was with a load balancer that the customer had in the network. But in that case, the errors were different, the problem was that the server was not recognizing the certificate used by the client, because it was altered by the load balancer. This does not seem to be the case now. Did they try to uninstall the client (with remove database and logs) and install again?  I am not confident that this will work either, but they could try/
